513
00:49:04,525 --> 00:49:06,443
Ain't he something, now?

514
00:49:07,486 --> 00:49:09,655
He's smart, Mr. Jingles.

515
00:49:09,863 --> 00:49:12,032
-Mr. Jingles?
-That his name.

516
00:49:12,407 --> 00:49:14,576
He whispered in my ear.

517
00:49:15,119 --> 00:49:16,203
Hey, captain...

518
00:49:16,370 --> 00:49:20,040
...could I have a box for my mouse
so he can sleep in here with me?

519
00:49:20,249 --> 00:49:22,918
Your English gets better
when you want something.

520
00:49:23,127 --> 00:49:25,045
Wanna see what else he can do?

521
00:49:26,547 --> 00:49:28,048
Watch, watch.

522
00:49:28,215 --> 00:49:31,260
Mr. Jingle? Mr. Jingle,
wanna play fetch?

523
00:49:31,510 --> 00:49:32,553
Wanna play fetch?

524
00:49:34,263 --> 00:49:36,181
Play fetch. Watch, watch.

525
00:49:55,993 --> 00:49:58,912
He fetch it every time. Every time.

526
00:49:59,079 --> 00:50:03,750
That's some smart mouse, Del.
Like he a circus mouse or something.

527
00:50:05,961 --> 00:50:09,131
Correct. That just what he is too.
He's a circus mouse.

528
00:50:09,339 --> 00:50:11,383
When I get out,
he'll make me rich.

529
00:50:11,758 --> 00:50:14,094
You just watch and see
if he don't do that.

530
00:50:14,428 --> 00:50:16,597
Play fetch? We play fetch again?

531
00:50:17,264 --> 00:50:19,099
Well, well, well.

532
00:50:19,558 --> 00:50:21,768
Looks like you found yourself
a new friend.

533
00:50:22,436 --> 00:50:23,770
Don't hurt him.

534
00:50:25,314 --> 00:50:27,774
-Okay?
-Is that the one I chased?

535
00:50:28,150 --> 00:50:29,818
Yeah, that's the one.

536
00:50:30,319 --> 00:50:33,614
Only Del says his name is Mr. Jingles.

537
00:50:34,656 --> 00:50:35,741
Is that so?

538
00:50:36,950 --> 00:50:38,619
Del's been asking for a box.

539
00:50:39,453 --> 00:50:43,248
Thinks the mouse will sleep in it,
I guess. Might keep it for a pet.

540
00:50:45,626 --> 00:50:46,919
What do you think?

541
00:50:48,128 --> 00:50:51,965
You know what?
We ought to find a cigar box...

542
00:50:52,466 --> 00:50:57,095
...and get some cotton batting
from the dispensary to line it with.

543
00:50:57,554 --> 00:50:59,223
Yeah.

544
00:50:59,389 --> 00:51:02,476
Yeah. That should do real nice.

545
00:51:11,818 --> 00:51:14,321
Man said get a cigar box.

546
00:51:23,914 --> 00:51:25,374
Morning.

547
00:51:30,212 --> 00:51:32,256
Hal, you wanted to see me?

548
00:51:32,506 --> 00:51:33,840
Yeah.

549
00:51:34,341 --> 00:51:35,884
Close the door.

550
00:51:43,183 --> 00:51:44,559
So you know...

551
00:51:46,395 --> 00:51:48,897
...you got a new prisoner
coming in here tomorrow.

552
00:51:50,023 --> 00:51:51,692
"William Wharton."

553
00:51:52,401 --> 00:51:54,069
He's what you call...

554
00:51:54,361 --> 00:51:56,363
...a problem child.

555
00:51:57,197 --> 00:52:00,909
Got "Billy the Kid" tattooed
on his left arm.

556
00:52:01,118 --> 00:52:05,205
Been rambling all over the state
last few years...

557
00:52:05,622 --> 00:52:07,833
...causing all kinds of trouble.

558
00:52:08,583 --> 00:52:10,544
Finally hit the big time.

559
00:52:11,920 --> 00:52:15,215
Killed three people in a holdup.

560
00:52:15,424 --> 00:52:17,551
One of them a pregnant woman.

561
00:52:20,053 --> 00:52:22,055
Bad news all around.

562
00:52:24,057 --> 00:52:25,559
Hal?

563
00:52:36,486 --> 00:52:37,738
It's a tumor, Paul.

564
00:52:39,406 --> 00:52:41,158
A brain tumor.

565
00:52:42,909 --> 00:52:44,578
They got...

566
00:52:44,911 --> 00:52:46,997
...X-ray pictures of it.

567
00:52:48,415 --> 00:52:50,917
It's the size of a lemon, they said.

568
00:52:53,628 --> 00:52:54,921
And...

569
00:52:56,089 --> 00:52:57,591
...way down...

570
00:52:59,426 --> 00:53:01,636
...deep inside,
where they can't operate.

571
00:53:03,680 --> 00:53:05,349
I haven't told her.

572
00:53:07,100 --> 00:53:09,102
I can't think how.

573
00:53:12,856 --> 00:53:14,983
For the life of me, Paul...

574
00:53:16,485 --> 00:53:19,488
...I can't think how
to tell my wife...

575
00:53:22,949 --> 00:53:24,951
...she's going to die.

576
00:54:23,468 --> 00:54:25,595
Oh.

577
00:54:30,267 --> 00:54:31,476
Aah.

578
00:54:32,936 --> 00:54:34,271
Aah!

579
00:54:43,864 --> 00:54:46,450
Oh!

580
00:54:50,036 --> 00:54:51,705
Oh, God.

581
00:54:52,372 --> 00:54:53,915
Oh, God.

582
00:54:57,794 --> 00:54:59,212
I'm going.

583
00:54:59,379 --> 00:55:03,383
-What?
-To see Dr. Bishop. I'm going.

584
00:55:03,717 --> 00:55:05,218
Today.

585
00:55:05,719 --> 00:55:08,638
Soon as we get that new inmate
squared away.

586
00:55:08,805 --> 00:55:10,307
That bad?

587
00:55:10,724 --> 00:55:12,142
Oh, yeah.

588
00:55:34,247 --> 00:55:36,416
The boy is doped to the gills.

589
00:55:37,792 --> 00:55:39,252
Hmm?

590
00:55:39,419 --> 00:55:40,629
Hand me them clothes.

591
00:55:43,673 --> 00:55:45,592
William Wharton?

592
00:55:46,009 --> 00:55:49,221
Hey! You put on these clothes now,
you hear?

593
00:55:57,312 --> 00:55:59,439
We're gonna have to do this.

594
00:56:00,649 --> 00:56:02,275
Hellraiser, huh?

595
00:56:02,484 --> 00:56:05,028
Look more like a limp noodle to me.

596
00:56:05,195 --> 00:56:08,281
Hey. Hey.

597
00:56:08,949 --> 00:56:12,744
You've been declared competent, son.
You know what that means?

598
00:56:13,453 --> 00:56:16,164
Means you're gonna ride the lightning.
Yeah.

599
00:56:17,207 --> 00:56:19,918
Percy, could you shut up,
give us a hand here?

600
00:56:20,794 --> 00:56:22,462
Hellraiser.

601
00:56:53,451 --> 00:56:54,953
You don't look so good.

602
00:56:56,913 --> 00:56:58,873
Look like you're running you a fever.

603
00:57:04,671 --> 00:57:06,256
Boss Edgecomb?

604
00:57:07,757 --> 00:57:09,676
I needs to see you down here, boss.

605
00:57:12,262 --> 00:57:15,765
I got things to tend to just now,
John Coffey. You just...

606
00:57:17,225 --> 00:57:20,604
You just stay still in your cell.

607
00:57:32,198 --> 00:57:33,408
E Block.

608
00:58:09,653 --> 00:58:11,154
Come on, let's go.

609
00:58:12,405 --> 00:58:14,491
Come on. Look alive, big boy.

610
00:58:29,172 --> 00:58:30,423
Careful.

611
00:58:33,927 --> 00:58:37,097
-Careful.
-Step up. Step up.

612
00:59:11,631 --> 00:59:13,925
Where you going? Where you going?

613
00:59:17,804 --> 00:59:19,139
Ain't this a party now?

614
00:59:19,431 --> 00:59:20,640
-Is it or what?
-Let him go.

615
00:59:20,849 --> 00:59:22,475
-Shoot him.
-See who you hit.

616
00:59:22,684 --> 00:59:24,644
-Shoot the son of a bitch.
-Shoot me!

617
00:59:24,811 --> 00:59:28,148
-Shoot him!
-Hit him, Percy! Goddamn it! Hit him.

618
00:59:28,356 --> 00:59:29,816
Hit me, you limp noodle.

619
00:59:30,024 --> 00:59:32,318
Hit him, Percy!
Goddamn it, hit him!

620
00:59:32,527 --> 00:59:35,488
-Come on, Percy. Hit me.
-Wharton, I'm warning you.

621
00:59:35,697 --> 00:59:38,533
-You warning me? Warn me now.
-I'm warning you!

622
00:59:38,742 --> 00:59:40,785
-You're warning me?!
-Shoot him!

623
00:59:40,994 --> 00:59:42,328
Well, come on--

624
00:59:48,918 --> 00:59:50,837
You're a big fucker.

625
00:59:51,171 --> 00:59:52,630
Where'd you come from?

626
01:00:03,224 --> 01:00:05,727
Come on, Dean. Come on, boy, get up.

627
01:00:05,935 --> 01:00:07,520
All right. Now, just breathe.

628
01:00:08,062 --> 01:00:10,190
That's it. Just breathe.
Just breathe.

629
01:00:12,025 --> 01:00:13,777
Breathe. Breathe, boy.

630
01:00:14,027 --> 01:00:16,988
-Didn't see it coming.
-Come on, boy, breathe.

631
01:00:17,197 --> 01:00:19,199
Come on. Just breathe.

632
01:00:22,035 --> 01:00:24,204
We thought he was doped.

633
01:00:25,455 --> 01:00:28,708
Didn't we? Didn't we, all of us,
think he was doped?

634
01:00:28,917 --> 01:00:30,668
You didn't ask?

635
01:00:31,961 --> 01:00:33,880
Well, I guess that's not a mistake...

636
01:00:34,214 --> 01:00:37,425
...you'll be needing to make again
anytime soon, is it?

637
01:00:51,481 --> 01:00:55,109
You go get Dean and Harry looked at.
Make sure they're all right.

638
01:00:55,568 --> 01:00:59,072
Percy, you make the report
to the warden for me.

639
01:00:59,280 --> 01:01:01,866
Say the situation's under control.
It's not a story.

640
01:01:02,075 --> 01:01:04,744
He won't appreciate you
drawing out the suspense.

641
01:01:04,911 --> 01:01:07,163
What about you?
You're about to collapse.

642
01:01:07,413 --> 01:01:10,750
I've got the Mile
till you all come back.

643
01:01:11,501 --> 01:01:13,461
Go on, now. Go.

644
01:01:21,135 --> 01:01:24,264
Come on, boy. Let's get you looked at.

645
01:01:49,873 --> 01:01:53,293
Boss, I needs to see you down here.

646
01:01:56,838 --> 01:02:00,091
This is not a good time, John Coffey...

647
01:02:00,300 --> 01:02:02,260
...not a good time at all.

648
01:02:02,468 --> 01:02:06,598
But I needs to see you, boss.
I needs to talk to you.

649
01:02:28,661 --> 01:02:29,954
Closer.

650
01:02:30,496 --> 01:02:32,540
Boss, you know you ain't
supposed to do that.

651
01:02:34,167 --> 01:02:36,169
Mind your business, Del.

652
01:02:45,803 --> 01:02:47,847
What do you want, John Coffey?

653
01:02:48,890 --> 01:02:50,016
Just to help it.

654
01:02:53,686 --> 01:02:55,104
Don't be afraid.

655
01:02:55,647 --> 01:02:56,689
Help!

656
01:02:57,523 --> 01:03:00,318
Help! John Coffey's
killing Boss Edgecomb!

657
01:03:00,485 --> 01:03:02,028
Help!

658
01:03:02,195 --> 01:03:05,448
-What are you doing?
-Help!

659
01:03:08,034 --> 01:03:09,869
Boss Howell! Help!

660
01:03:10,578 --> 01:03:12,330
Boss Stanton! Somebody, come!

661
01:03:12,664 --> 01:03:14,624
Help!

662
01:03:22,590 --> 01:03:24,425
Aah!

663
01:03:31,057 --> 01:03:33,267
Help! Boss Howell! Boss Stanton!

664
01:03:33,476 --> 01:03:36,437
Somebody, come!
John Coffey's killing Boss Edgecomb!

665
01:03:36,646 --> 01:03:39,273
-Del, for christ sakes, shut up!
-Hel--

666
01:04:25,862 --> 01:04:28,114
What did you just do to me?

667
01:04:30,074 --> 01:04:31,784
I helped it.

668
01:04:32,827 --> 01:04:34,454
Didn't I help it?

669
01:04:35,580 --> 01:04:37,790
I just took it back, is all.

670
01:04:38,624 --> 01:04:41,085
Awful tired now, boss.

671
01:04:41,627 --> 01:04:43,296
Dog-tired.

672
01:05:07,445 --> 01:05:10,490
Boss, what that man do to you?

673
01:05:50,321 --> 01:05:52,281
Ahh.

674
01:06:12,927 --> 01:06:15,721
Hey, honey. How you feeling?

675
01:06:17,515 --> 01:06:20,268
Oh, not too bad.

676
01:06:21,519 --> 01:06:23,271
What did the doctor say?

677
01:06:25,523 --> 01:06:27,233
Oh, you know doctors.

678
01:06:27,692 --> 01:06:29,569
Gobbledygook, mostly.

679
01:06:30,695 --> 01:06:32,071
Gobbledygook.

680
01:06:47,295 --> 01:06:48,921
Having stew tonight.

681
01:06:59,223 --> 01:07:00,933
What are you doing?

682
01:07:07,607 --> 01:07:09,483
What does it feel like?

683
01:07:10,359 --> 01:07:12,778
Well, I know what it feels like.

684
01:07:16,449 --> 01:07:18,326
It feels great.

685
01:07:52,777 --> 01:07:54,654
-Paul.
-Yeah?

686
01:07:55,112 --> 01:07:57,823
-Not that I'm complaining...
-Uh-huh.

687
01:07:58,991 --> 01:08:02,703
...but we haven't gone four times
in one night since we were 19.

688
01:08:02,954 --> 01:08:05,331
-Yeah, we did, at your mom's.
-Mm-hmm.

689
01:08:06,832 --> 01:08:08,834
Wanna tell me what's going on?

690
01:08:12,630 --> 01:08:14,006
Well...

691
01:08:15,299 --> 01:08:17,301
...see, the thing is...

692
01:08:18,511 --> 01:08:22,056
...never actually made it in
to Dr. Bishop's yesterday.

693
01:08:25,351 --> 01:08:28,020
Brutal, Paul. Listen.

694
01:08:28,229 --> 01:08:32,692
I'm thinking of taking the morning
off sick. You cover the fort for me?

695
01:08:33,734 --> 01:08:36,028
That's swell. Thanks.

696
01:08:36,195 --> 01:08:38,864
Yeah, no, I'm sure I'll feel better.

697
01:08:39,073 --> 01:08:41,701
Okay. Okay.

698
01:08:47,081 --> 01:08:49,041
You're sure you ought to do this?

699
01:08:50,668 --> 01:08:52,878
I'm not sure what I'm sure of.

700
01:09:09,729 --> 01:09:12,732
Burt, you got some company.

701
01:09:13,399 --> 01:09:14,984
Can I offer you a cold drink?

702
01:09:15,234 --> 01:09:18,321
Oh, yes, ma'am. A cold drink
would be fine. Thank you.

703
01:09:18,654 --> 01:09:21,741
Mr. Hammersmith, your office said
I might find you at home.

704
01:09:21,949 --> 01:09:23,617
Hope I'm not troubling you.

705
01:09:24,285 --> 01:09:26,412
Well, that depends, Mr...?

706
01:09:26,579 --> 01:09:30,624
Paul Edgecomb. I'm E Block supervisor
up on Cold Mountain.

707
01:09:31,834 --> 01:09:33,210
The Green Mile.

708
01:09:33,419 --> 01:09:36,547
Yeah, I've heard of it.
Lost a few clients your way.

709
01:09:37,298 --> 01:09:39,925
I'd like to ask you about one of them.

710
01:09:41,177 --> 01:09:43,179
-Have a seat.
-Thank you.

711
01:09:47,933 --> 01:09:49,685
Which client?

712
01:09:51,145 --> 01:09:53,939
Now you got my curiosity aroused.

713
01:09:54,148 --> 01:09:56,525
-John Coffey.
-Ah.

714
01:09:56,692 --> 01:09:58,110
Coffey.

715
01:09:58,277 --> 01:09:59,487
He causing you problems?

716
01:09:59,945 --> 01:10:03,532
No. Can't say he is. He doesn't like
the dark and cries on occasion...

717
01:10:03,741 --> 01:10:05,618
...but other than that...

718
01:10:05,785 --> 01:10:09,080
He cries, does he?
Well, got a lot to cry about, I'd say.

719
01:10:09,288 --> 01:10:10,831
You know what he did.

720
01:10:11,499 --> 01:10:13,542
I read the court transcript.

721
01:10:14,460 --> 01:10:17,213
-Thank you, missus.
-My pleasure.

722
01:10:18,089 --> 01:10:21,384
Kids! Lunch is about ready.
Y'all come on up.

723
01:10:21,634 --> 01:10:22,927
Coming, Mama!

724
01:10:23,135 --> 01:10:26,263
What exactly are you
trying to find out?

725
01:10:26,847 --> 01:10:29,183
I've wondered if he did anything
like that before.

726
01:10:30,643 --> 01:10:32,645
Why? Has he said anything?

727
01:10:32,812 --> 01:10:35,981
No, but a man who does
a thing like that...

728
01:10:36,190 --> 01:10:40,111
...has often developed a taste for it
over time. It occurred to me...

729
01:10:40,319 --> 01:10:44,198
...that it might be easy enough
to follow his back trail. Find out.

730
01:10:44,990 --> 01:10:48,786
A man his size, and colored to boot,
can't be that hard to trace.

731
01:10:48,994 --> 01:10:51,997
You'd think so, but you'd be wrong.

732
01:10:52,164 --> 01:10:54,333
Believe me, we tried.

733
01:10:55,167 --> 01:10:57,336
Like he'd dropped out of the sky.

734
01:10:58,170 --> 01:10:59,588
How can that be?

735
01:10:59,839 --> 01:11:04,009
We're in a depression.
A third of the country's out of work.

736
01:11:04,218 --> 01:11:08,264
People are drifting by the thousands,
looking for jobs, for greener grass.

737
01:11:08,514 --> 01:11:11,642
Even a giant like Coffey
wouldn't get noticed everywhere.

738
01:11:12,393 --> 01:11:14,728
Not until he kills
a couple of little girls.

739
01:11:15,563 --> 01:11:17,189
He is...

740
01:11:17,523 --> 01:11:19,567
...strange, I admit.

741
01:11:19,942 --> 01:11:24,238
But there doesn't seem to be
any real violence in him.

742
01:11:24,697 --> 01:11:27,116
I know violent men, Mr. Hammersmith.

743
01:11:27,366 --> 01:11:30,202
I deal with them day in and day out.

744
01:11:30,995 --> 01:11:33,664
You didn't come to ask me
whether he killed before.

745
01:11:33,873 --> 01:11:36,792
You came to see if I think
he did it at all.

746
01:11:38,210 --> 01:11:39,879
Do you?

747
01:11:41,088 --> 01:11:43,257
One seldom sees
a less ambiguous case.

748
01:11:43,466 --> 01:11:45,551
He was found with the victims
in his arms.

749
01:11:45,718 --> 01:11:47,553
And yet you defended him.

750
01:11:48,554 --> 01:11:51,140
Everyone is entitled to a defense.

751
01:11:51,557 --> 01:11:53,184
Kids! Lunch!

752
01:11:53,392 --> 01:11:54,685
Y'all listen to your mama

753
01:11:59,315 --> 01:12:00,900
I'll tell you something.

754
01:12:01,942 --> 01:12:05,571
And you listen close too, because it
might be something you need to know.

755
01:12:05,738 --> 01:12:07,114
I'm listening.

756
01:12:08,574 --> 01:12:10,493
We had us a dog.

757
01:12:10,659 --> 01:12:12,703
Just a sweet mongrel.

758
01:12:12,912 --> 01:12:14,413
You know the kind.

759
01:12:15,748 --> 01:12:19,210
Well, in many ways,
a good mongrel dog is like a Negro.

760
01:12:20,085 --> 01:12:21,837
You get to know it.

761
01:12:22,046 --> 01:12:26,425
Often, you get to love it.
It is of no particular use...

762
01:12:26,592 --> 01:12:30,137
...but you keep it around
because you think it loves you.

763
01:12:31,639 --> 01:12:35,768
If you're lucky, Mr. Edgecomb, you
never have to find out any different.

764
01:12:36,852 --> 01:12:39,063
My wife and I were not so lucky.

765
01:12:41,023 --> 01:12:42,566
Caleb, come here for a second.

766
01:12:43,943 --> 01:12:45,152
Come here.

767
01:12:46,612 --> 01:12:47,863
Please, son.

768
01:12:49,448 --> 01:12:51,951
He still has the one good eye.

769
01:12:53,285 --> 01:12:55,579
