02:53:37,323 --> 02:53:39,742
One thing I don't understand.

1776
02:53:39,993 --> 02:53:41,744
You said you and Jan...

1777
02:53:41,995 --> 02:53:45,498
...had a grown son in 1935.

1778
02:53:45,832 --> 02:53:47,333
Is that right?

1779
02:53:47,709 --> 02:53:49,669
The math doesn't work, does it?

1780
02:53:55,174 --> 02:53:57,927
Do you feel up to taking a walk?

1781
02:54:18,656 --> 02:54:20,033
Watch your step.

1782
02:54:20,533 --> 02:54:22,869
Now let your eyes adjust.

1783
02:54:34,547 --> 02:54:35,757
There.

1784
02:54:38,384 --> 02:54:41,262
Hey. Wake up, old fella.

1785
02:54:41,554 --> 02:54:42,805
Wake up.

1786
02:54:46,392 --> 02:54:50,271
Paul, it isn't. It can't be.

1787
02:54:54,400 --> 02:54:55,777
Come over here, boy.

1788
02:54:56,277 --> 02:54:58,655
Come on over here and see this lady.

1789
02:55:01,574 --> 02:55:04,577
That can't be Mr. Jingles.

1790
02:55:27,266 --> 02:55:29,852
Go on, you can do it.

1791
02:55:36,943 --> 02:55:41,447
This isn't exactly the Mouseville
we had in mind, is it?

1792
02:55:42,198 --> 02:55:46,119
But we make do. Don't we, old fella?

1793
02:55:52,625 --> 02:55:56,295
I think Mr. Jingles
happened by accident.

1794
02:55:56,713 --> 02:56:01,592
I think when we electrocuted Del,
and it all went so badly...

1795
02:56:01,801 --> 02:56:04,137
...well, John could feel that,
you know.

1796
02:56:04,387 --> 02:56:07,807
And I think a part of...

1797
02:56:07,974 --> 02:56:10,810
...whatever magic was inside of him...

1798
02:56:10,977 --> 02:56:14,313
...just leapt into my tiny friend here.

1799
02:56:15,481 --> 02:56:17,483
As for me...

1800
02:56:18,651 --> 02:56:21,154
...John had to give me
a part of himself...

1801
02:56:21,487 --> 02:56:23,656
...a gift, the way he saw it...

1802
02:56:23,990 --> 02:56:27,410
...So that I could see for myself
what Wild Bill had done.

1803
02:56:29,829 --> 02:56:31,998
When John did that...

1804
02:56:33,499 --> 02:56:35,835
...when he took my hand...

1805
02:56:36,836 --> 02:56:40,673
...a part of the power
that worked through him...

1806
02:56:41,674 --> 02:56:43,509
...Spilled into me.

1807
02:56:43,885 --> 02:56:45,678
He what?

1808
02:56:46,179 --> 02:56:49,682
He infected you with life?

1809
02:56:51,267 --> 02:56:53,603
It's as good a word as any.

1810
02:56:55,104 --> 02:56:58,024
He infected us both,
didn't he, Mr. Jingles?

1811
02:56:58,191 --> 02:56:59,692
With life.

1812
02:57:03,696 --> 02:57:06,866
I'm 108 years old, Elaine.

1813
02:57:07,033 --> 02:57:11,454
I was 44 the year that John Coffey
walked the Green Mile.

1814
02:57:14,373 --> 02:57:18,127
You mustn't blame John.
He couldn't help what happened.

1815
02:57:18,377 --> 02:57:22,924
He was just a force of nature.

1816
02:57:23,382 --> 02:57:27,553
Oh, I've lived to see
some amazing things, Ellie.

1817
02:57:28,554 --> 02:57:31,557
Another century come to pass.

1818
02:57:31,808 --> 02:57:33,684
But I've...

1819
02:57:34,310 --> 02:57:38,731
I've had to see my friends and
loved ones die off through the years.

1820
02:57:39,148 --> 02:57:41,234
Hal and Melinda...

1821
02:57:41,651 --> 02:57:43,069
...Brutus Howell...

1822
02:57:43,236 --> 02:57:45,947
...my wife, my boy.

1823
02:57:48,908 --> 02:57:50,743
And you, Elaine.

1824
02:57:51,744 --> 02:57:53,579
You'll die too.

1825
02:57:55,081 --> 02:57:59,460
And my curse is knowing
that I'll be there to see it.

1826
02:58:00,920 --> 02:58:03,339
It's my atonement, you see.

1827
02:58:03,923 --> 02:58:05,591
It's my punishment...

1828
02:58:05,842 --> 02:58:08,469
...for letting John Coffey
ride the lightning.

1829
02:58:10,179 --> 02:58:12,974
For killing a miracle of God.

1830
02:58:14,475 --> 02:58:17,270
Almighty, everlasting God...

1831
02:58:17,562 --> 02:58:19,939
...the source of all being and life...

1832
02:58:20,106 --> 02:58:22,525
You'll be gone like all the others.

1833
02:58:22,692 --> 02:58:24,485
I'll have to stay.

1834
02:58:26,487 --> 02:58:30,700
Oh, I'll die eventually.
Of that I'm sure.

1835
02:58:31,450 --> 02:58:35,454
I have no illusions of immortality.

1836
02:58:35,788 --> 02:58:38,416
But I will have wished for death...

1837
02:58:38,583 --> 02:58:41,210
...long before death finds me.

1838
02:58:42,295 --> 02:58:46,132
In truth, I wish for it already.

1839
02:58:58,227 --> 02:59:00,229
Mr. Jingles?

1840
02:59:09,155 --> 02:59:11,324
Where you been?

1841
02:59:11,657 --> 02:59:15,077
Been worried about you, boy.
You hungry?

1842
02:59:15,912 --> 02:59:18,331
Let's go see if we can't find you
something to eat.

1843
02:59:19,498 --> 02:59:23,169
A few crumbs anyway.
I know you'd like that.

1844
02:59:24,670 --> 02:59:26,005
Look at you.

1845
02:59:27,673 --> 02:59:31,594
I lie in bed most nights
thinking about it.

1846
02:59:31,802 --> 02:59:33,846
And I wait.

1847
02:59:34,555 --> 02:59:37,475
I think about all the people
I've loved...

1848
02:59:37,683 --> 02:59:39,852
...now long gone.

1849
02:59:40,353 --> 02:59:43,022
I think about my beautiful Jan...

1850
02:59:43,189 --> 02:59:46,192
...how [ lost her so many years ago.

1851
02:59:47,610 --> 02:59:52,198
And I think about all of us walking
our own Green Mile...

1852
02:59:52,448 --> 02:59:55,117
...each in our own time.

1853
02:59:56,202 --> 02:59:59,372
But one thought
more than any other...

1854
02:59:59,580 --> 03:00:02,208
...keeps me awake most nights:

1855
03:00:03,376 --> 03:00:07,380
If he could make a mouse
live so long...

1856
03:00:07,713 --> 03:00:10,883
...how much longer do I have?

1857
03:00:14,220 --> 03:00:17,014
We each owe a death.

1858
03:00:17,223 --> 03:00:19,725
There are no exceptions.

1859
03:00:20,476 --> 03:00:22,478
But, oh, God...

1860
03:00:23,396 --> 03:00:25,189
...sometimes...

1861
03:00:25,731 --> 03:00:29,402
...the Green Mile seems so long.
